THE SUBTRIBE 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9750E15FBC1EA52FAF6A838" baseAuthorityName="Li, Zhou &amp; Schillhammer" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[1124,1280,1567,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">PHILONTHINA</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2094B589D9750E17FC83EA08FAA3A8BB" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="689" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" type="description">
<paragraph id="6831E602D9750E17FC83EA08FAA3A8BB" blockId="8.[806,1421,1605,1903]" lastBlockId="10.[806,1421,1575,1719]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="689" pageId="8" pageNumber="687">
The present phylogenetic analyses are the first contribution to the phylogeny of the whole subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9750E15FC83EACEFC5BA895" baseAuthorityName="Li, Zhou &amp; Schillhammer" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[806,941,1667,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">Philonthina</taxonomicName>
based on broad representatives and morphological characters. The phylogenetic result supported the polyphyly of the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9750E15FB5AEA8DFA7FA8DA" baseAuthorityName="Li, Zhou &amp; Schillhammer" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[1279,1417,1728,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">Philonthina</taxonomicName>
; because the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9750E15FC59EA93FB75A8FF" box="[1020,1155,1758,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Erichsonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9750E15FC59EA93FB75A8FF" box="[1020,1155,1758,1779]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="687">Erichsonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the sister group of the remaining 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9750E15FC7BEAB0FB9AA91F" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[990,1132,1789,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Staphylinini">Staphylinini</taxonomicName>
(very distant from the rest of 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9750E15FC29EB51FBE1A93E" baseAuthorityName="Li, Zhou &amp; Schillhammer" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[908,1047,1820,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">Philonthina</taxonomicName>
). Another recent phylogenetic analysis (
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9750E15FC38EB77FAE2A95C" author="Solodovnikov AY &amp; Newton AF" box="[925,1300,1850,1872]" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" pagination="398 - 441" refId="ref22162" refString="Solodovnikov AY, Newton AF. 2005. Phylogenetic placement of Arrowinini trib. N. within the subfamily Staphylininae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae), with revision of the relict South African genus Arrowinus and description of its larva. Systematic Entomology 30: 398 - 441." type="journal article" year="2005">Solodovnikov &amp; Newton, 2005</bibRefCitation>
) and the earlier morphological study (
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9750E17FB33EB14FF3EA831" author="Smetana A &amp; Davies A" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="689" pageId="8" pageNumber="687" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref22064" refString="Smetana A, Davies A. 2000. Reclassification of the north temperate taxa associated with Staphylinus sensu Lato, including comments on relevant subtribes of staphylinini (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). American Museum Novitates 3287: 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="2000">Smetana &amp; Davies, 2000</bibRefCitation>
) converged on the conclusion that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FF35EA08FEE1A856" box="[144,279,1605,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Erichsonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9770E17FF35EA08FEE1A856" box="[144,279,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="689">Erichsonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the basal groups of 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FF35EA29FEE8A876" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[144,286,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Staphylinini">Staphylinini</taxonomicName>
rather than a member of 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FDCDEA29FD05A876" baseAuthorityName="Li, Zhou &amp; Schillhammer" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[616,755,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">Philonthina</taxonomicName>
. This can be easily understood when considering the unique characters of 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FE28EAECFDE2A8BA" box="[397,532,1697,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Erichsonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9770E17FE28EAECFDE2A8BA" box="[397,532,1697,1718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="689">Erichsonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including absence of transparent apical membrane of labrum, presence of well-developed infraorbital ridge and weakly sclerotized postcoxal process of pronotal hypomeron, mentum with two anterolateral setae on each side, ligula more or less bilobed, the position of the aedeagus in abdomen, and the biramous paramere in some species of this genus. This genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FB15EA6AFAC1A830" box="[1200,1335,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Erichsonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9770E17FB15EA6AFAC1A830" box="[1200,1335,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="689">Erichsonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be moved out from the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FB39EA08FAD5A857" baseAuthorityName="Li, Zhou &amp; Schillhammer" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[1180,1315,1605,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">Philonthina</taxonomicName>
to eliminate the polyphyly of 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FB8FEA29FB47A876" baseAuthorityName="Li, Zhou &amp; Schillhammer" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[1066,1201,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">Philonthina</taxonomicName>
and it is expected that the systematic status of 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FB04EACEFADEA894" box="[1185,1320,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Erichsonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9770E17FB04EACEFADEA894" box="[1185,1320,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="689">Erichsonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be elevated to subtribe or tribe level in the future.
</paragraph>
